9
00:00:53,521 --> 00:00:56,722
  traditional wood slat baskets 
         are containers         

10
00:00:56,724 --> 00:00:59,925
  used to carry and gather food 
        during a harvest.       

11
00:00:59,927 --> 00:01:03,529
   they're also used in retail  
  settings to display produce,  

12
00:01:03,531 --> 00:01:10,269
  providing the consumer with a 
 farm-fresh marketing aesthetic.

13
00:01:10,271 --> 00:01:14,807
     since the 1800, farmers    
   have used wood slat baskets  

14
00:01:14,809 --> 00:01:16,742
   to hold and transport food.  

15
00:01:16,744 --> 00:01:20,546
 today, they still come in handy
        at harvest time.        

16
00:01:20,548 --> 00:01:24,683
 wood slat baskets are made out 
  of american sweet gum trees.  

17
00:01:24,685 --> 00:01:28,421
   first, the freshly cut logs  
     are sprayed with water     

18
00:01:28,423 --> 00:01:30,622
so they don't dry out and decay.

19
00:01:30,624 --> 00:01:34,827
  one at a time, spiked rollers 
  grab the logs and turn them,  

20
00:01:34,829 --> 00:01:38,030
            as knives           
     shave off all the bark.    

21
00:01:38,032 --> 00:01:41,033
        the de-barked log       
      rolls down a conveyor     

22
00:01:41,035 --> 00:01:44,102
            to be cut           
    to the specified length.    

23
00:01:44,104 --> 00:01:47,707
    the wood spins on a lathe   
 as a blade cuts into the wood, 

24
00:01:47,709 --> 00:01:50,176
  producing long, thin sheets.  

25
00:01:50,178 --> 00:01:51,711
                     ♪♪         

26
00:01:51,713 --> 00:01:57,116
   technicians pull the sheets  
     forward and stack them.    

27
00:01:57,118 --> 00:01:59,851
the sheets move through rollers.

28
00:01:59,853 --> 00:02:04,056
   the rollers feed the stack   
 to a long guillotine-type blade

29
00:02:04,058 --> 00:02:06,525
  which chops them into slats.  

30
00:02:06,527 --> 00:02:09,461
      once all of the slats     
         have been cut,         

31
00:02:09,463 --> 00:02:12,264
      the slats are stacked     
    and checked for quality.    

32
00:02:12,266 --> 00:02:14,132
                     ♪♪         

33
00:02:14,134 --> 00:02:15,801
 technicians use these patterns 

34
00:02:15,803 --> 00:02:19,071
   to configure the wood slats  
         and form a web.        

35
00:02:19,073 --> 00:02:25,010
                     ♪♪         

36
00:02:25,012 --> 00:02:28,681
   the technician distributes   
 the slats in a specific order, 

37
00:02:28,683 --> 00:02:32,684
  which will add strength when  
the web is formed into a basket.

38
00:02:32,686 --> 00:02:35,421
      he uses a staple gun      
        to place staples        

39
00:02:35,423 --> 00:02:40,559
   into the center of the web   
      to hold it together.      

40
00:02:40,561 --> 00:02:42,294
       at another station,      

41
00:02:42,296 --> 00:02:45,764
   workers evaluate and grade   
     narrower strips of wood    

42
00:02:45,766 --> 00:02:51,103
 that will be formed into bands 
  to hold the baskets together. 

43
00:02:51,105 --> 00:02:53,638
  then, using a basket machine, 

44
00:02:53,640 --> 00:02:58,577
    technicians form the web    
         into a basket.         

45
00:02:58,579 --> 00:03:01,513
     the machine wraps bands    
        around the basket       

46
00:03:01,515 --> 00:03:04,650
        and staples them        
     to reinforce the shape.    

47
00:03:04,652 --> 00:03:07,319
           in seconds,          
     the basket takes shape.    

48
00:03:07,321 --> 00:03:11,389
 once it's complete, the baskets
  are removed from the machine  

49
00:03:11,391 --> 00:03:13,392
 and placed on a conveyor belt. 

50
00:03:13,394 --> 00:03:16,662
       at another station,      
   technicians build a basket   

51
00:03:16,664 --> 00:03:18,931
 with a base made of solid wood.

52
00:03:18,933 --> 00:03:22,735
   this base will provide the   
basket with additional strength.

53
00:03:22,737 --> 00:03:26,071
      workers arrange slats     
      to build the basket.      

54
00:03:26,073 --> 00:03:30,409
  automated staplers secure the 
  slats to the solid-wood base. 

55
00:03:30,411 --> 00:03:34,213
       bands are attached       
  to hold the basket together.  

56
00:03:34,215 --> 00:03:37,950
   a technician places the rim  
  of the basket into a machine  

57
00:03:37,952 --> 00:03:40,820
     that drives thick wire     
        into the basket.        

58
00:03:40,822 --> 00:03:44,022
   the machine's formers bend   
     the wire into a handle     

59
00:03:44,024 --> 00:03:45,491
        and cut the ends.       

60
00:03:45,493 --> 00:03:48,027
      the technician turns      
         the basket over        

61
00:03:48,029 --> 00:03:50,963
      for a matching handle     
      on the opposite side.     

62
00:03:50,965 --> 00:03:54,700
the baskets now take a slow trip
        through a dryer.        

63
00:03:54,702 --> 00:03:58,838
 this step removes the majority 
  of the moisture in the wood.  

64
00:03:58,840 --> 00:04:01,306
         once complete,         
       the produce baskets      

65
00:04:01,308 --> 00:04:03,042
    slide down a steel slope.   

66
00:04:03,044 --> 00:04:05,444
          a technician          
     evaluates their quality    

67
00:04:05,446 --> 00:04:07,246
  and stacks them accordingly.  

68
00:04:07,248 --> 00:04:09,648
 next, the lids are constructed.

69
00:04:09,650 --> 00:04:12,918
  technicians place wood slats  
   in the slots of a conveyor.  

70
00:04:12,920 --> 00:04:17,322
this positions them to be formed
  into squares, known as mats.  

71
00:04:17,324 --> 00:04:19,858
the conveyor takes them forward,

72
00:04:19,860 --> 00:04:22,294
  and a device creates staples  
           from wire,           

73
00:04:22,296 --> 00:04:23,863
   punching them into the mats  

74
00:04:23,865 --> 00:04:27,599
   to secure the arrangement.   

75
00:04:27,601 --> 00:04:31,670
  meanwhile, a worker prepares  
        the lids' hoops.        

76
00:04:31,672 --> 00:04:34,072
        first, he steams        
        gum wood strips,        

77
00:04:34,074 --> 00:04:35,541
  which makes the wood pliable. 

78
00:04:35,543 --> 00:04:37,610
          then he tucks         
       one end of the wood      

79
00:04:37,612 --> 00:04:39,678
    into the revolving wheel    
         of the machine,        

80
00:04:39,680 --> 00:04:41,547
      which shapes the wood     
          into a hoop.          

81
00:04:41,549 --> 00:04:47,219
    the ends are then secured   
          with staples.         

82
00:04:47,221 --> 00:04:53,425
   an assembler fits the hoop   
  around a circular platform... 

83
00:04:53,427 --> 00:04:55,894
   and places the mat on top.   

84
00:04:55,896 --> 00:04:57,696
      the platform rotates      

85
00:04:57,698 --> 00:05:01,366
 as a stapler attaches the hoop 
          to the slats.         

86
00:05:01,368 --> 00:05:04,703
   the mat must now be trimmed  
        flush to the hoop       

87
00:05:04,705 --> 00:05:09,508
 so that it will fit more neatly
    on the rim of the basket.   

88
00:05:09,510 --> 00:05:13,579
   to do so, another assembler  
  places the corners of the mat 

89
00:05:13,581 --> 00:05:18,717
  under a semi-circular blade,  
  chopping off the excess wood. 

90
00:05:20,521 --> 00:05:25,524
 the wood slat lid is now ready 
    to be put on the basket.    

91
00:05:25,526 --> 00:05:28,059
 a device bends wire into a loop

92
00:05:28,061 --> 00:05:32,264
   that will be used to fasten  
     the lid to the basket.     

93
00:05:32,266 --> 00:05:37,269
   this factory can make up to  
 6,000 wood slat baskets a day. 

94
00:05:37,271 --> 00:05:41,140
  that's a lot of empty baskets 
            to fill.            

95
00:05:49,483 --> 00:05:54,019
                     ♪♪         

96
00:05:54,021 --> 00:05:56,355
            narrator:           
     for thousands of years,    

97
00:05:56,357 --> 00:05:58,890
 we've used bells to make noise.

98
00:05:58,892 --> 00:06:00,892
       the concept behind       
         them is simple.        

99
00:06:00,894 --> 00:06:03,295
       a clapper or hammer      
      strikes the bell wall     

100
00:06:03,297 --> 00:06:06,232
       creating vibrations      
      that disturb the air.     

101
00:06:06,234 --> 00:06:08,700
     the disturbance causes     
       the ringing sound.       

102
00:06:08,702 --> 00:06:13,838
       it's not high tech,      
   but it can be high-pitched.  

103
00:06:13,840 --> 00:06:15,040
                     ♪♪         

104
00:06:15,042 --> 00:06:18,176
         every bell has         
       a distinctive ring.      

105
00:06:18,178 --> 00:06:20,111
        from the festive        
     jingle of sleigh bells,    

106
00:06:20,113 --> 00:06:22,114
 to the clang of the boxing bell

107
00:06:22,116 --> 00:06:25,050
           that marks           
    the beginning of a fight.   

108
00:06:25,052 --> 00:06:27,386
  even the cow bell has a sound 

109
00:06:27,388 --> 00:06:29,989
that's not quite like any other.

110
00:06:29,991 --> 00:06:32,258
        the bell's shape        
        and the material        

111
00:06:32,260 --> 00:06:35,527
      it's made from affect     
        the ring's pitch.       

112
00:06:35,529 --> 00:06:37,329
to make a cow bell, an assembler

113
00:06:37,331 --> 00:06:41,266
uses two flared steel components
         to form a cone.        

114
00:06:41,268 --> 00:06:46,472
   he inserts a handle between  
   the two parts at the top...  

115
00:06:46,474 --> 00:06:49,074
       and welds the seams      
        of the bell shell       

116
00:06:49,076 --> 00:06:54,079
 to hold the two parts together.

117
00:06:54,081 --> 00:06:58,149
    then he welds the handle    
      to the cow bell body.     

118
00:06:58,151 --> 00:07:00,752
the handle contains a small loop

119
00:07:00,754 --> 00:07:05,224
  that extends inside the bell  
    body to hold the clapper.   

120
00:07:05,226 --> 00:07:08,093
       this strip of steel      
   is about to be transformed   

121
00:07:08,095 --> 00:07:11,030
       into sleigh bells.       

122
00:07:11,032 --> 00:07:13,798
       an upper die forces      
         the steel strip        

123
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:16,501
into dies on a rotating platter.

124
00:07:16,503 --> 00:07:18,904
          the dies form         
     the metal into a shape     

125
00:07:18,906 --> 00:07:22,174
 that resembles an open flower. 

126
00:07:22,176 --> 00:07:26,111
          ball bearings         
      funnel into a shoot.      

127
00:07:26,113 --> 00:07:28,981
     the ball bearings land     
       in the open flowers      

128
00:07:28,983 --> 00:07:32,184
         on the platter.        

129
00:07:32,186 --> 00:07:35,320
      the upper die closes      
    the petals of the flower    

130
00:07:35,322 --> 00:07:37,456
  creating a round sleigh bell. 

131
00:07:37,458 --> 00:07:39,992
          the rattle of         
    the interior ball bearing   

132
00:07:39,994 --> 00:07:42,127
     will create the sound.     

133
00:07:42,129 --> 00:07:45,930
          a device pops         
     the bell out of the die    

134
00:07:45,932 --> 00:07:50,135
      and the sleigh bells      
        fall into a bin.        

135
00:07:50,137 --> 00:07:53,205
      once the sleigh bells     
     are plated with nickel,    

136
00:07:53,207 --> 00:07:57,142
  they are ready for rattling.  

137
00:07:57,144 --> 00:08:01,480
  at another station, a boxing  
   bell begins to takes shape.  

138
00:08:01,482 --> 00:08:04,683
 an assembler transfers the bell
           to a punch           

139
00:08:04,685 --> 00:08:06,618
 that cuts a hole in the center.

140
00:08:06,620 --> 00:08:08,753
the punch forces it on to a form

141
00:08:08,755 --> 00:08:11,757
          that contours         
    the area around the hole.   

142
00:08:11,759 --> 00:08:16,494
       oil keeps the metal      
   lubricated as it's forming.  

143
00:08:16,496 --> 00:08:19,297
        the gongs tumble        
       around in a machine      

144
00:08:19,299 --> 00:08:26,372
 with vibrating ceramic stones, 
      detergent, and water.     

145
00:08:26,374 --> 00:08:30,442
      the stones scrub off      
the oil and rub off rough edges.

146
00:08:30,444 --> 00:08:32,177
     after about 10 minutes,    

147
00:08:32,179 --> 00:08:35,313
     the gongs emerge smooth    
           and clean.           

148
00:08:35,315 --> 00:08:38,083
      they land in the tub      
      of ground corn cobs.      

149
00:08:38,085 --> 00:08:41,053
 the corn absorbs residual water

150
00:08:41,055 --> 00:08:44,456
     as it pulsates in this     
       vibratory machine.       

151
00:08:44,458 --> 00:08:48,927
       a technician places      
      the gongs in an oven.     

152
00:08:48,929 --> 00:08:52,130
       this heat treatment      
   rearranges the crystalline   

153
00:08:52,132 --> 00:08:56,000
     structures of the steel    
         and hardens it.        

154
00:08:56,002 --> 00:08:58,003
 making the steel more resilient

155
00:08:58,005 --> 00:09:01,874
  will also make the gong sound 
   more resonant when struck.   

156
00:09:01,876 --> 00:09:06,611
                     ♪♪         

157
00:09:06,613 --> 00:09:09,081
      the gongs are sprayed     
     with a powder coating.     

158
00:09:09,083 --> 00:09:11,350
         when baked on,         
      the powder particles      

159
00:09:11,352 --> 00:09:13,552
     will form a protective     
        skin on the metal       

160
00:09:13,554 --> 00:09:17,422
      and provide the gongs     
     with a uniform finish.     

161
00:09:17,424 --> 00:09:19,424
                     ♪♪         

162
00:09:19,426 --> 00:09:22,494
    a powder coat is sprayed    
    on the bell's baseplate,    

163
00:09:22,496 --> 00:09:27,099
 and an adhesive-backed company 
  logo is applied to the back.  

164
00:09:27,101 --> 00:09:29,434
         posts have been        
     installed on the front     

165
00:09:29,436 --> 00:09:31,436
 for assembling the other parts.

166
00:09:31,438 --> 00:09:34,506
        a brass lever for       
    operating the bell hammer   

167
00:09:34,508 --> 00:09:38,176
   and the mechanism that will  
     swing it, called a dog.    

168
00:09:38,178 --> 00:09:42,247
      the assembler rivets      
      the dog to the lever      

169
00:09:42,249 --> 00:09:46,184
      and hooks one end of      
   a spring to the mechanism.   

170
00:09:46,186 --> 00:09:48,987
       he fastens another       
      spring to the hammer      

171
00:09:48,989 --> 00:09:51,857
         and then hooks         
    the end to the baseplate.   

172
00:09:51,859 --> 00:09:56,995
     he installs the hammer     
      on one of the posts.      

173
00:09:56,997 --> 00:10:01,867
  using a push nut, he secures  
     the hammer to the post.    

174
00:10:01,869 --> 00:10:05,137
                     ♪♪         

175
00:10:05,139 --> 00:10:08,340
       he hooks the lever       
     spring on the baseplate    

176
00:10:08,342 --> 00:10:13,345
    and slides the lever onto   
  a post just under the hammer. 

177
00:10:13,347 --> 00:10:18,283
     another push nut locks     
       the lever in place.      

178
00:10:18,285 --> 00:10:21,819
 the assembler pulls the lever, 
     examining the movement,    

179
00:10:21,821 --> 00:10:24,489
     adjusting accordingly.     

180
00:10:24,491 --> 00:10:29,027
                     ♪♪         

181
00:10:29,029 --> 00:10:30,762
      he now adds the gong,     

182
00:10:30,764 --> 00:10:33,565
    aligning the center hole    
      to the threaded post      

183
00:10:33,567 --> 00:10:38,503
 in the middle of the backplate.

184
00:10:38,505 --> 00:10:42,307
     he screws on a fastener    
   to hold the gong in place.   

185
00:10:42,309 --> 00:10:45,110
      he pulls the lever to     
     confirm that the hammer    

186
00:10:45,112 --> 00:10:47,713
hits the gong and makes a noise.

187
00:10:47,715 --> 00:10:50,515
                     ♪♪         

188
00:10:50,517 --> 00:10:54,786
   finally this boxing bell is  
     now ready for the ring.    

189
00:10:54,788 --> 00:10:56,989
         [ bell dings ]         

190
00:11:04,598 --> 00:11:09,401
                     ♪♪         

191
00:11:09,403 --> 00:11:12,070
            narrator:           
at the turn of the 20th century,

192
00:11:12,072 --> 00:11:16,074
  gigantic gyroscopes were used 
       to stabilize ships.      

193
00:11:16,076 --> 00:11:17,943
even though they were effective,

194
00:11:17,945 --> 00:11:20,678
     the devices were large     
           and heavy.           

195
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:23,815
        today, gyroscopes       
      are smaller, lighter,     

196
00:11:23,817 --> 00:11:29,221
    and are highly effective    
          stabilizers.          

197
00:11:29,223 --> 00:11:32,490
    the boat on the left has    
     a gyroscopic stabilizer    

198
00:11:32,492 --> 00:11:36,228
  that counteracts wave action. 

199
00:11:36,230 --> 00:11:40,966
     different boats require    
   different sized gyroscopes.  

200
00:11:40,968 --> 00:11:44,169
       this complex device      
       includes a flywheel      

201
00:11:44,171 --> 00:11:50,842
      and a hydraulic brake     
  which controls its movement.  

202
00:11:50,844 --> 00:11:52,911
         a large hammer         
        forge has pounded       

203
00:11:52,913 --> 00:11:55,847
 the flywheels into this shape. 

204
00:11:55,849 --> 00:11:58,983
       the process begins       
         on a cnc lathe         

205
00:11:58,985 --> 00:12:02,120
    that shapes this aircraft   
      quality alloyed steel     

206
00:12:02,122 --> 00:12:05,190
       to perimeters with       
    very small tolerances --    

207
00:12:05,192 --> 00:12:09,927
        roughly one third       
 the diameter of a hair strand. 

208
00:12:09,929 --> 00:12:12,463
           the shafts,          
      or bearing journals,      

209
00:12:12,465 --> 00:12:15,267
     are put into a machine     
       which form the axis      

210
00:12:15,269 --> 00:12:18,503
on which the flywheel will spin.

211
00:12:21,541 --> 00:12:24,076
         a diamond wheel        
       grinds the journal       

212
00:12:24,078 --> 00:12:28,146
to the specified size and shape.

213
00:12:28,148 --> 00:12:29,881
         once complete,         

214
00:12:29,883 --> 00:12:31,817
    the flywheel is balanced.   

215
00:12:31,819 --> 00:12:34,286
       a state of the art       
        balancing machine       

216
00:12:34,288 --> 00:12:39,691
       i.d.s exactly which      
     spots need adjustment.     

217
00:12:39,693 --> 00:12:42,827
   highly trained technicians   
       carefully grind off      

218
00:12:42,829 --> 00:12:46,698
    small quantities of steel   
     in the identified spots    

219
00:12:46,700 --> 00:12:51,770
    before putting the object   
       through more tests.      

220
00:12:51,772 --> 00:12:55,440
     with tolerances of just    
     a fraction of an ounce,    

221
00:12:55,442 --> 00:12:57,509
  even a tiny particle of dust  

222
00:12:57,511 --> 00:12:59,978
          can throw off         
     the flywheel's balance.    

223
00:12:59,980 --> 00:13:01,846
                     ♪♪         

224
00:13:01,848 --> 00:13:05,517
         a probe locates        
  this aluminum cast hemisphere 

225
00:13:05,519 --> 00:13:10,722
        so that a machine       
    can begin processing it.    

226
00:13:10,724 --> 00:13:13,057
         the hemisphere         
       will form one half       

227
00:13:13,059 --> 00:13:16,194
      of the enclosure that     
    will house the flywheel.    

228
00:13:16,196 --> 00:13:19,464
      it must be precision      
        machined so that        

229
00:13:19,466 --> 00:13:22,334
      it can form a perfect     
         airtight seal.         

230
00:13:22,336 --> 00:13:25,670
       made of aluminum to      
    decrease overall weight,    

231
00:13:25,672 --> 00:13:28,272
     the airtight enclosure     
      is one of the crucial     

232
00:13:28,274 --> 00:13:30,475
   elements of this gyroscope.  

233
00:13:30,477 --> 00:13:32,477
  once it's completely sealed,  

234
00:13:32,479 --> 00:13:37,082
all the air will be vacuumed out
  and helium will be pumped in. 

235
00:13:37,084 --> 00:13:40,218
      because helium is so      
     much lighter than air,     

236
00:13:40,220 --> 00:13:42,754
      the flywheel will be      
    able to spin much faster    

237
00:13:42,756 --> 00:13:48,760
        due to radically        
      diminished friction.      

238
00:13:48,762 --> 00:13:52,430
    machining with horizontal   
     and vertical cnc tools     

239
00:13:52,432 --> 00:13:55,567
     and a vertical grinder     
   brings the bearing housing   

240
00:13:55,569 --> 00:13:58,704
         within reach of        
    the required parameters.    

241
00:13:58,706 --> 00:14:02,908
                     ♪♪         

242
00:14:02,910 --> 00:14:05,777
      a technician attaches     
        the vacuum valves       

243
00:14:05,779 --> 00:14:11,917
   which will allow air to be   
   removed from the enclosure.  

244
00:14:11,919 --> 00:14:14,853
        then he installs        
       some of the sensors      

245
00:14:14,855 --> 00:14:18,924
     that carefully monitor     
     the gyroscope's status.    

246
00:14:18,926 --> 00:14:21,392
  he applies a specified torque 

247
00:14:21,394 --> 00:14:25,663
           to tighten           
     the component in place.    

248
00:14:25,665 --> 00:14:28,332
   a generous amount of grease  
           is applied           

249
00:14:28,334 --> 00:14:30,936
       to the large o-ring      
       that fits perfectly      

250
00:14:30,938 --> 00:14:35,673
        into a groove in        
   the lip of one hemisphere.   

251
00:14:35,675 --> 00:14:38,410
     the o-ring will ensure     
       a vacuum tight seal      

252
00:14:38,412 --> 00:14:42,547
   when the two hemispheres of  
  the enclosure come together.  

253
00:14:42,549 --> 00:14:46,017
                     ♪♪         

254
00:14:46,019 --> 00:14:49,688
   these heavy duty eye bolts   
    form an attachment point    

255
00:14:49,690 --> 00:14:52,691
    for lifting, which helps    
       move the gyroscope       

256
00:14:52,693 --> 00:14:56,494
     in and out of position.    

257
00:14:56,496 --> 00:14:59,097
         once everything        
     has been put together,     

258
00:14:59,099 --> 00:15:04,902
     the technician connects    
 the flywheel to the enclosure. 

259
00:15:04,904 --> 00:15:07,705
        he begins bolting       
     an inner and outer set     

260
00:15:07,707 --> 00:15:12,177
   of retainer rings in place.  

261
00:15:12,179 --> 00:15:17,983
    these rings will support    
     the flywheel assembly.     

262
00:15:17,985 --> 00:15:20,919
         faster spinning        
    in its vacuum containment   

263
00:15:20,921 --> 00:15:22,720
    will allow the gyroscope    

264
00:15:22,722 --> 00:15:25,056
       to achieve the same      
       stabilizing effect       

265
00:15:25,058 --> 00:15:27,659
        as a much larger,       
        heavier flywheel        

266
00:15:27,661 --> 00:15:30,462
   spinning at a slower speed.  

267
00:15:30,464 --> 00:15:36,267
                     ♪♪         

268
00:15:36,269 --> 00:15:38,870
      the technician joins      
        the sub-assembly        

269
00:15:38,872 --> 00:15:41,006
    to the second hemisphere,   

270
00:15:41,008 --> 00:15:45,543
        carefully lifting       
   and lowering it into place   

271
00:15:45,545 --> 00:15:51,215
         before bolting         
the enclosure securely together.

272
00:15:51,217 --> 00:15:54,619
  but the gyroscope stabilizer  
         isn't done yet.        

273
00:15:54,621 --> 00:15:56,221
  it still needs to be mounted  

274
00:15:56,223 --> 00:15:58,690
        to a specialized        
      foundation assembly.      

275
00:16:05,966 --> 00:16:10,434
                     ♪♪         

276
00:16:10,436 --> 00:16:13,104
            narrator:           
early attempts to use gyroscopes

277
00:16:13,106 --> 00:16:14,705
      for stabilizing boats     

278
00:16:14,707 --> 00:16:17,041
       weren't successful       
     because the gyroscopes     

279
00:16:17,043 --> 00:16:19,043
     were too big and heavy.    

280
00:16:19,045 --> 00:16:22,247
   but thanks to some state of  
 the art technical innovations, 

281
00:16:22,249 --> 00:16:25,050
     a new breed of lighter,    
       smaller gyroscopes       

282
00:16:25,052 --> 00:16:27,318
         can easily keep        
       a boat deck steady,      

283
00:16:27,320 --> 00:16:31,656
     even in rough weather.     

284
00:16:31,658 --> 00:16:34,592
        a technician uses       
      a specialized device      

285
00:16:34,594 --> 00:16:36,394
        to measure three        
        important factors       

286
00:16:36,396 --> 00:16:38,596
 of the flywheel's performance. 

287
00:16:38,598 --> 00:16:42,733
         concentricity,         
  eccentricity, and clearance.  

288
00:16:42,735 --> 00:16:44,803
           this means           
      he's checking to see      

289
00:16:44,805 --> 00:16:46,604
       if the component is      
        spinning smoothly       

290
00:16:46,606 --> 00:16:50,341
        and consistently        
      without any wobbling.     

291
00:16:50,343 --> 00:16:54,880
      he spins the flywheel     
       slowly on its axis,      

292
00:16:54,882 --> 00:17:00,685
      evaluating the meter      
          accordingly.          

293
00:17:00,687 --> 00:17:03,221
        the gimbal shaft        
      will allow the sphere     

294
00:17:03,223 --> 00:17:07,425
     to tilt back and forth,    
      stabilizing the boat.     

295
00:17:07,427 --> 00:17:10,628
      a technician installs     
    a set of steel dowel pins   

296
00:17:10,630 --> 00:17:14,566
    that will hold the brake    
       cylinders in place.      

297
00:17:14,568 --> 00:17:20,572
                     ♪♪         

298
00:17:20,574 --> 00:17:24,042
   he uses a press to install   
      the spherical bearing     

299
00:17:24,044 --> 00:17:25,843
  and urethane that will permit 

300
00:17:25,845 --> 00:17:31,383
  the sphere to shift its axial 
 rotation and absorb vibration. 

301
00:17:31,385 --> 00:17:33,652
                     ♪♪         

302
00:17:33,654 --> 00:17:36,321
        with the bearing        
     and protector in place,    

303
00:17:36,323 --> 00:17:38,122
   he mounts the gimbal shaft   

304
00:17:38,124 --> 00:17:41,326
           securely to          
    the gyroscope enclosure.    

305
00:17:41,328 --> 00:17:44,262
 a total of 10 heavy duty bolts 

306
00:17:44,264 --> 00:17:50,535
        are tightened to        
   the specified torque value.  

307
00:17:50,537 --> 00:17:53,337
      next, the technician      
       installs the cover       

308
00:17:53,339 --> 00:17:56,408
     and bolts it in place,     
      sealing the enclosure     

309
00:17:56,410 --> 00:17:59,678
       and fully rounding       
        out its exterior.       

310
00:17:59,680 --> 00:18:02,680
                     ♪♪         

311
00:18:02,682 --> 00:18:06,017
  once the valve is installed,  
       he checks for leaks      

312
00:18:06,019 --> 00:18:09,087
       by spraying helium       
    outside of the enclosure.   

313
00:18:09,089 --> 00:18:13,825
                     ♪♪         

314
00:18:13,827 --> 00:18:16,827
    this meter will register    
     the presence of helium     

315
00:18:16,829 --> 00:18:20,865
     if the lightweight gas     
  sneaks in through any cracks. 

316
00:18:20,867 --> 00:18:22,634
                     ♪♪         

317
00:18:22,636 --> 00:18:25,102
this magnetically mounted sensor

318
00:18:25,104 --> 00:18:27,172
           will allow           
    the technician to conduct   

319
00:18:27,174 --> 00:18:31,576
  final trim balance, ensuring  
   a vibration-free operation.  

320
00:18:31,578 --> 00:18:34,646
       it's vital to keep       
     vibration to a minimum     

321
00:18:34,648 --> 00:18:36,981
          to make sure          
   that the gyroscope provides  

322
00:18:36,983 --> 00:18:40,918
   a smooth, stable boat ride.  

323
00:18:40,920 --> 00:18:43,988
     now it's time to attach    
     the cooling components.    

324
00:18:43,990 --> 00:18:48,259
        when the flywheel       
      spins at 9,000 rpms,      

325
00:18:48,261 --> 00:18:49,594
       it generates heat.       

326
00:18:49,596 --> 00:18:54,199
   sea water mixed with glycol  
    is used to keep it cool.    

327
00:18:57,070 --> 00:18:59,670
       the enclosure will       
       sit in a framework       

328
00:18:59,672 --> 00:19:01,272
    known as the foundation,    

329
00:19:01,274 --> 00:19:04,743
 which is made of cast aluminum.

330
00:19:04,745 --> 00:19:06,678
     once the gimbal shafts     

331
00:19:06,680 --> 00:19:08,813
         are set within         
      their lower housings,     

332
00:19:08,815 --> 00:19:10,081
       which are situated       

333
00:19:10,083 --> 00:19:12,216
        on either side of       
         the foundation,        

334
00:19:12,218 --> 00:19:14,753
      a technician installs     
       the upper housings       

335
00:19:14,755 --> 00:19:17,488
         and bolts them         
       securely in place.       

336
00:19:17,490 --> 00:19:21,559
                     ♪♪         

337
00:19:21,561 --> 00:19:24,361
      this aluminum section     
        of the foundation       

338
00:19:24,363 --> 00:19:26,764
          will support          
    the hydraulic brake arm,    

339
00:19:26,766 --> 00:19:30,335
       a key component of       
    the gyroscope's function.   

340
00:19:31,905 --> 00:19:34,638
     the brake support piece    
          also doubles          

341
00:19:34,640 --> 00:19:37,441
     as a support structure     
     for the heat exchanger,    

342
00:19:37,443 --> 00:19:39,977
      which is an important     
   element of the gyroscope's   

343
00:19:39,979 --> 00:19:41,513
         cooling system.        

344
00:19:41,515 --> 00:19:44,649
                     ♪♪         

345
00:19:44,651 --> 00:19:47,986
     the technician installs    
     the brake arm cylinder.    

346
00:19:47,988 --> 00:19:50,855
       this helps the gyro      
     perform in all weather     

347
00:19:50,857 --> 00:19:54,592
       and at all speeds.       

348
00:19:54,594 --> 00:19:58,196
    he installs the hydraulic   
   lines for the brake system.  

349
00:19:58,198 --> 00:20:01,199
      they manage the flow      
       of hydraulic fluid       

350
00:20:01,201 --> 00:20:05,536
   to and from the cylinders.   

351
00:20:05,538 --> 00:20:08,439
     the solenoids that make    
      up the major elements     

352
00:20:08,441 --> 00:20:11,209
    of this assembly dictate    
        braking pressure        

353
00:20:11,211 --> 00:20:15,613
   to the hydraulic cylinder.   

354
00:20:15,615 --> 00:20:18,616
          the drive box         
       controls the brake,      

355
00:20:18,618 --> 00:20:21,553
          the start up,         
    and speed of the flywheel   

356
00:20:21,555 --> 00:20:24,355
     and the angle sensors,     
   which detect the roll rate   

357
00:20:24,357 --> 00:20:26,758
     and angle of the boat.     

358
00:20:26,760 --> 00:20:29,494
                     ♪♪         

359
00:20:29,496 --> 00:20:31,963
   the drive box receives data  

360
00:20:31,965 --> 00:20:36,033
 from the rest of the gyroscope.

361
00:20:36,035 --> 00:20:39,037
       this wiring harness      
      serves as the conduit     

362
00:20:39,039 --> 00:20:42,574
   of information to and from   
   the components of the unit.  

363
00:20:42,576 --> 00:20:47,645
                     ♪♪         

364
00:20:47,647 --> 00:20:51,048
 once assembled, the technician 
     installs the remaining     

365
00:20:51,050 --> 00:20:55,853
    support arm on the other    
     side of the gyroscope.     

366
00:20:55,855 --> 00:20:58,122
 before the assembled gyroscope 

367
00:20:58,124 --> 00:20:59,991
 gets its aluminum cover piece, 

368
00:20:59,993 --> 00:21:03,127
   it must undergo a thorough   
    factory assessment test.    

369
00:21:03,129 --> 00:21:06,330
   the test ensures that it's   
        fully functioning       

370
00:21:06,332 --> 00:21:09,400
and meets all design parameters.

371
00:21:09,402 --> 00:21:13,270
    there is no question that   
     gyroscopic stabilizers     

372
00:21:13,272 --> 00:21:16,007
    help maintain level heads   
            on deck.            

